answers:
## SPARQL Queries

**1. Which medication was prescribed by Dr. William Abernathy for patient Alice Thompson on 2022-02-14?**

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT ?medicationName
WHERE {
  ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientId ; syn:first "Alice"; syn:last "Thompson".
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter ; syn:patientId ?patientId ; syn:isPerformedBy ?provider.
  ?provider syn:id ?providerId ; syn:first "William" ; syn:last "Abernathy".
  ?medication a syn:Medication ; syn:isPrescribedDuring ?encounter ; syn:description ?medicationName .
  FILTER(?encounter syn:date = xsd:date "2022-02-14")
}
```

**2. What was the total cost incurred by Medicare for all patients in the simulation?**

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT SUM(?totalCost)
WHERE {
  ?payer a syn:Payer ; syn:name "Medicare".
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter ; syn:isCoveredBy ?payer ; syn:baseEncounterCost ?totalCost .
}
```

**3. What are the names of patients who have had a pneumonia diagnosis within the past year?**

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?firstName ?lastName
WHERE {
  ?patient a syn:Patient ; syn:first ?firstName ; syn:last ?lastName.
  ?condition a syn:Condition ; syn:isDiagnosedDuring ?encounter ; syn:patientId ?patientId.
  ?encounter syn:patientId ?patientId ; syn:date ?encounterDate.
  FILTER(?condition syn:code = "Pneumonia (disorder)"^^snomed: )
  FILTER(?encounterDate > xsd:date "2023-11-20")
}
```

**4. Which medication has the highest total cost incurred by Aetna?**

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT ?medicationName ?totalCost
WHERE {
  ?payer a syn:Payer ; syn:name "Aetna".
  ?medication a syn:Medication ; syn:isCoveredBy ?payer ; syn:description ?medicationName ; syn:totalCost ?totalCost .
}
ORDER BY DESC(?totalCost)
LIMIT 1
```

**5. What is the average age of patients covered by Aetna?**

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT AVG(?age) as ?averageAge
WHERE {
  ?payer a syn:Payer ; syn:name "Aetna".
  ?patient syn:isCoveredBy ?payer ; syn:birthdate ?birthDate.
  BIND(xsd:duration(?birthDate, now()) as ?age)
}
```

question: Please provide me the encounters that are related to the device with code 337414009.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?description WHERE { ?device a syn:Device; syn:code '337414009'^^snomed:; syn:encounterId ?encounterid. ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:id ?encounterid; syn:description ?description. }
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> 
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> 
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX> 
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI> 
PREFIX ct: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm> 
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC> 

SELECT DISTINCT ?condition ?provider ?org ?encounter ?date ?organizationName ?speciality ?providerName ?city 
WHERE 
{
 ?condition a syn:Condition .
 ?condition syn:code '7319003'^^snomed: .
 ?condition syn:isDiagnosedDuring ?encounter .
 ?encounter syn:isPerformedBy ?provider .
 ?provider syn:isAffiliatedWith ?org .
 ?provider syn:speciality ?speciality .
 ?provider syn:id ?providerId .
 ?encounter syn:performed?date ?date .
 ?encounter syn:description ?encounter .
 ?org syn:name ?organizationName .
 ?org syn:city ?city .
 
 ## find patient from this condition
 ?condition syn:hasPatientRecord ?payerTransition .
 ?payerTransition syn:hasPatient ?patient .
 ## find claim based on patient and service date
 ?encounter syn:isCoveredBy ?claim .
 ?claim syn:hasPatient ?patient .
 ?claim syn:serviceDate ?serviceDate .
 ## find the start date of patient's enrollment into payer
 ?payerTransition syn:startYear ?startYear .
 ## find the payer transaction in this year
 FILTER (?startYear <= ?serviceDate^^xsd:date) .
 ## find payer 
 ?payerTransition syn:hasPayerRecord ?payer .
 ?payer syn:name ?payerName .
}

question: What is the amount of the claims transferred with the claim transaction ID 1ef6fdcb-5c71-61fd-3481-b8d5616d4b30?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?amount WHERE { ?claimtransaction a syn:ClaimTransaction;syn:id '1ef6fdcb-5c71-61fd-3481-b8d5616d4b30'^^uuid:; syn:amount ?amount.}
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX dicom: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#dicom:DICOM-DCM>
PREFIX dicom: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#dicom:DICOM-SOP>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

# What is the amount claimed for procedure '26060-7'?
SELECT ?amount
WHERE {
  # Claim with transaction.
  ?tx a syn:ClaimTransaction ; syn:procedureCode "26060-7"^^snomed: ; syn:isTransactionFor ?claim.

  # Get claimed amount from claim's parent id.
  ?claim syn:isTransactionFor ?parentClaim.
	?parentId a syn:Claim ; syn:id ?parentClaim; syn:id ?parent; syn:amountCovered ?amount.

  # Print human-friendly result with parent transaction id from original query.
FILTER regex(str("?2", ?parentID), r"([0-9A-Fa-f]{8}(-[0-9A-Fa-f]{4}){3}-[0-9A-Fa-f]{12})", "i")

}
```

question: When was the service date of the claim with the ID b441ef2a-bc13-eca3-a194-982a95dae652?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?serviceDate WHERE { ?claim a syn:Claim;syn:id 'b441ef2a-bc13-eca3-a194-982a95dae652'^^uuid:; syn:serviceDate ?serviceDate.}
answers:
## Answer and Explanation:

Here is a corrected SPARQL query based on the given prompt: 

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?serviceDate 
WHERE {
  ?claim a syn:Claim ;
        syn:id uuid: "b441ef2a-bc13-eca3-a194-982a95dae652" ;
        syn:serviceDate ?serviceDate .
}
```

### Explanation:

1. **Prefixes**: 
    - The query starts by declaring the prefixes used in the following code. These shortcuts help to improve readability and avoid repeating long URIs.
2. **SELECT clause**: 
    - This clause specifies the data we want to retrieve from the query. Here, we want to select the `?serviceDate` of the claim.
3. **WHERE clause**:
    - This clause defines the criteria that the data must meet to be included in the results. In this case, the criteria are:
        - The element `?claim` must be a `syn:Claim` instance.
        - The `?claim` must have an `id` equal to the `uuid: "b441ef2a-bc13-eca3-a194-982a95dae652"`.
        - The `?claim` must have a `serviceDate` attribute, which we want to retrieve as `?serviceDate`.

4. **Running the query**: 
    - This query can be executed against a database containing the data from the given ontology. 
    - If the database contains the claim with the specified ID, the query will return the service date of that claim.
    - If the claim is not found, the query will return an empty result.

question: Who has been treated with the procedure of code 268556000?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?first ?last WHERE { ?procedure a syn:Procedure; syn:code '268556000'^^snomed:; syn:patientId ?patientId. ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientid; syn:first ?first ; syn:last ?last ; }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

SELECT DISTINCT ?patient_name WHERE {
    ?procedure a syn:Procedure ;
        syn:code '268556000'^^snomed: .
    ?encounter a syn:Encounter ;
        syn:procedure ?procedure .
    ?patient a syn:Patient ;
        syn:id ?patientId .
    ?encounter syn:patient ?patientId ;
        syn:isAbout ?patient .
    ?patient syn:first ?first_name ;
            syn:last ?last_name .
    BIND (concat(?first_name, ' ', ?last_name) as ?patient_name) .
}
```

answers:
'```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

question: What is the description of the condition with code 840544004?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?description WHERE { ?condition a syn:Condition; syn:code '840544004'^^snomed:; syn:description ?description }
answers:
##  SPARQL query to retrieve relevant information:

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
# ... other prefixes as needed ...

SELECT ?encounterId ?encounterDescription ?allergyDescription WHERE {
  ?allergy a syn:Allergy ;
          syn:description ?allergyDescription ;
          syn:encounterId ?encounterId .
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter ;
              syn:description ?encounterDescription ;
              syn:id ?encounterId .
  
  ## Filtering conditions (replace with your specific filters)
  FILTER(?allergyDescription = 'Animal dander (substance)'^^pl )
}
``` 

**Explanation:**

This SPARQL query retrieves information about encounters related to a specific allergy. It uses several core concepts from the Synthea ontology:

* `syn:Allergy`: represents an allergy instance.
* `syn:encounterId`: identifies the encounter associated with the allergy.
* `syn:Encounter`: represents an encounter instance.
* `syn:description`: describes both the encounter and the allergy.

The query filters encounters based on the `allergyDescription`, which is set to 'Animal dander (substance)' in this example. You can modify this filter to match the specific allergy you are interested in.

The query then retrieves the description of both the encounter and the allergy. 

**Remember to replace the following:**

* `'Animal dander (substance)'` with the specific description of the allergy you are looking for.
* `snomed:` with the appropriate prefix for the allergy code system.

question: What patients are associated with the claim transaction a584ab65-6ba0-ec35-2317-7ea3d849a5f9?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?first ?last WHERE { ?claimtransaction a syn:ClaimTransaction;syn:id 'a584ab65-6ba0-ec35-2317-7ea3d849a5f9'^^uuid:; syn:patientId ?patientId. ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientId; syn:first ?first; syn:last ?last.}
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

```sparql
SELECT DISTINCT ?patientName ?patientId
WHERE {
    ?patient a syn:Patient;
    syn:id ?patientId;
    syn:first ?patientName.

    ?claim a syn:Claim;
    syn:patientId ?patientId.

    ?claimTransaction a syn:ClaimTransaction;
    syn:claimId ?claimId.

    ?claimTransaction syn:claimId ?claimId;
    syn:claimTransactionType ?claimTransactionType.

    FILTER (?claimTransactionType = "PAYMENT")
}
```

```sparql

**[Q8]:** Which organization has the highest utilization among all providers?

**[SPARQL8]:**
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?organizationId (SUM(?utilization) AS ?totalUtilization)
WHERE {
  ?provider a syn:Provider ;
             syn:isAffiliatedWith ?organization .
  ?provider syn:utilization ?utilization .
  ?organization syn:id ?organizationId
}
GROUP BY ?organizationId
ORDER BY DESC(?totalUtilization)
LIMIT 1
```

**[Q11]:** What is the total cost of all encounters performed in July 2015?

}
```

answers:
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org.1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC> 
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX ct: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>

SELECT DISTINCT ?patientID ?name ?totalCost ?quantity ?description WHERE {
  ?patient syn:hasPatientRecord ?record .
  ?record syn:hasPayer ?payer .
  ?payer syn:name ?name .
  ?patient syn:id ?patientID .  
  ?record syn:hasEncounter ?encounter. 
	?encounter syn:isPrescribedFor ?patient. 

  { ?encounter syn:isPrescribedDuring ?med . } UNION 
  { ?encounter syn:hasOrdered ?med . }

  ?med syn:id ?medId. 
	?med syn:code ?med_code.  # get the product code of the given medication
	?med snomed: ?description.  # Get the description of medication.

  # Check if the product code matches the codes for inhalers	
	FILTER (?med_code = "767179000"^^snomed: OR ?med_code = "52125003"^^snomed: OR ?med_code = "182513004"^^snomed: OR ?med_code = "40528004"^^snomed:)

  ?encounter syn:isPerformedBy ?provider.
	?provider a syn:Provider . 

  # Extract the cost and quantity from the claim or claim transaction 	
  OPTIONAL { ?encounter syn:hasClaim ?claim. ?claim syn:totalCost ?totalCost. }
	OPTIONAL { ?encounter syn:hasClaim ?claimTransaction. ?claimTransaction syn:amountCovered ?totalCost.  } 
  OPTIONAL { ?med syn:dispense ?quantity . }

  FILTER (lang(?description) = 'en') 	
}

## Which medications will be prescribed in 2022 and beyond to treat patients with Diabetes without any allergy to Sulfonylureas?

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>

PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> 

SELECT DISTINCT ?name ?patientName

?allergy syn:hasPatient ?pat.
?pat syn:name ?patientName. ?med syn:code ?name .
FILTER ( ?condition syn:code = 'Type 2 diabetes mellitus (disorder)') . 
FILTER(?encounter syn:startDateTime > "2021-12-31T23:59:59.999"^^xsd:dateTime). }

**[Query #5]** 
## Which conditions have been diagnosed for patients 65 and older who have had no immunizations since they turned 65?
**SPARQL Query**:
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC> 

SELECT DISTINCT ?condLabel
WHERE { 
?patient syn:birthdate ?birthDateOfMonth .
FILTER( ?birthDateOfMonth < "1959-12-31T00:00:00.000-05:00"^^xsd:dateTime &&  ?birthDateOfMonth >=  "1948-01-01T05:00:00.000-05:00"^^xsd:dateTime  ). 
?condition syn:isAbout  ?patient . ?condition syn:code ?condCode .

# check that there is no record of immunizations since patient turned 65
# for a patient record
?record syn:patient ?patient .

# for a condition record
?condRecord syn:hasSubject ?record . ?condRecord syn:subjectId ?patient . 
?condRecord syn:condition ?condition . ?condRecord syn:isDiagnosedOn  ?condDiagnosedOn .

# no immunization after the birthdate for 65 years
FILTER NOT EXISTS 
  { ?immRecord syn:hasSubject ?record . 
    ?immRecord syn:subjectId ?patient . ?immRecord syn:immunization ?imm. 
    ?imm syn:dateTime  ?immDate . FILTER (?immDate > ?condDiagnosedOn) 
  }.

}
```

PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT ?patientName
WHERE {

```

question: Please provide me the number of immunizations uncovered by the payer Anthem.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?uncoveredImmunizations WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'Anthem'^^pl:; syn:uncoveredImmunizations ?uncoveredImmunizations. }
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

# How many patients had an immunization for "influenza virus vaccine"?
SELECT COUNT(?id)
WHERE {  ?imm a syn:Immunization . ?imm snomed:code ct:"197914003"^^snomed: ; syn:patientId ?id. }
 

#How old was patient #243 at their first immunization event?
SELECT (xsd:integer(?age)) as ?age
WHERE {  ?imm a syn:Immunization ; syn:patientId uuid:"243-49b983e5-9216-4511-ad33-8843c2d82420" . ?imm syn:dateTime  ?imm_date . 
		?pat a syn:Patient ; syn:id uuid:"243-49b983e5-9216-4511-ad33-8843c2d82420" ; syn:birthdate ?bir_date . 
		BIND (xsd:integer(YEAR(?imm_date) - YEAR(?bir_date)))  as ?age  }

#What fraction of all immunizations were not covered by insurance?
SELECT (xsd:decimal(?total / ?num)) as ?frac
WHERE {  ?pt a syn:Patient .
		{ SELECT (COUNT(?id) as ?total) WHERE { ?imm a syn:Immunization ; syn:patientId ?pt . }}
		{ SELECT (COUNT(?id) as ?num) WHERE { ?imm a syn:Immunization ; syn:patientId ?pt ; syn:payerCoverage 1 . } }}

#What were the five most common conditions that were found alongside immunizations?
SELECT ?d as ?desc , (COUNT(?d) as ?n)
WHERE { ?imm a syn:Immunization . ?con a syn:Condition ; 
	  syn:encounterId ?immId ;  snomed:code ?d. FILTER(?desc != pl:"Current Illness").}
GROUP BY  ?desc
ORDER BY DESC(?n) LIMIT 5

answers:

question: Who is associated with the organization LIFE CARE CENTER OF WILBRAHAM?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT DISTINCT ?first ?last WHERE { ?organization a syn:Organization; syn:id ?organizationId; syn:name 'LIFE CARE CENTER OF WILBRAHAM'^^pl:. ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:organizationId ?organizationId; syn:patientId ?patientId. ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientId; syn:first ?first; syn:last ?last. }
answers:
```turtle
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

SELECT DISTINCT ?patientName ?lastName WHERE {
  ?organization a syn:Organization ; syn:name "LIFE CARE CENTER OF WILBRAHAM"^^pl.
  ?provider syn:isAffiliatedWith ?organization.
  ?encounter syn:performedBy ?provider.
  ?patient syn:hasEncounter ?encounter.
  ?patient syn:last ?lastName.
  ?patient syn:first ?firstName.
  BIND(CONCAT(?firstName, " ", ?lastName) AS ?patientName).
}
```

question: Please provide me the number of procedures uncovered by the payer Blue Cross Blue Shield.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?uncoveredProcedures WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'Blue Cross Blue Shield'^^pl:; syn:uncoveredProcedures ?uncoveredProcedures. }
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT (COUNT(?procedure) AS ?count) WHERE {
  ?payer a syn:Payer ;
  syn:name 'Blue Cross Blue Shield'^^pl .
  
  ?payer syn:hasCovered ?encounter .
  ?encounter syn:hasOrdered ?procedure .
  
  FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?encounter syn:isCoveredBy ?procedure . }
}
## Find all patients who had a flu vaccine encounter after the start_date and before the end_date.
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
SELECT ?patient WHERE {
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter ;
  syn:isOrderedDuring ?immunization .
  ?immunization a syn:Immunization ;
  syn:code "88"^^cvx .  # Flu vaccine CVX code
  
  ?encounter syn:isPerformedDuring ?start_date, ?end_date .
  FILTER(?start_date >= "2015-01-01"^^xsd:date && ?end_date <= "2015-12-31"^^xsd:date) .
  
  ?encounter syn:isPerformedBy ?provider .
  ?provider syn:isAffiliatedWith ?organization .
  
  ?encounter syn:isAbout ?patient .
}
```

question: Give me the base cost of the immunization SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19) vaccine  mRNA  spike protein  LNP  preservative free  100 mcg/0.5mL dose.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT DISTINCT ?cost WHERE { ?immunization a syn:Immunization; syn:description 'SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19) vaccine  mRNA  spike protein  LNP  preservative free  100 mcg/0.5mL dose'^^pl:; syn:cost ?cost. }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
SELECT DISTINCT ?baseCost
WHERE {
  ?immunization a syn:Immunization ;
    syn:description 'SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19) vaccine  mRNA  spike protein  LNP  preservative free  100 mcg/0.5mL dose.'^^pl ;
    syn:baseCost ?baseCost.
}
```

**Query Breakdown:**

**PREFIX:** Declares the prefixes used in the query to shorten URI references.
**SELECT DISTINCT:** Indicates that the query will return distinct values for the variable `?baseCost`.
**WHERE:** Introduces the graph pattern to be matched.
**?immunization a syn:Immunization:** Matches instances of the `syn:Immunization` class.
**syn:description 'SARS-COV-2 (COVID-19) vaccine  mRNA  spike protein  LNP  preservative free  100 mcg/0.5mL dose.'^^pl:** Matches instances with the specified description, using the `pl:` prefix for the plain literal value.
**syn:baseCost ?baseCost:** Retrieves the value of the `syn:baseCost` property as the variable `?baseCost`.

question: How long does lisinopril 10 MG Oral Tablet effect last?
sparql: No answer possible based on given input
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?duration
WHERE {
  ?medication a syn:Medication ; syn:code 'lisinopril 10 MG Oral Tablet'^xsd:string ; syn:description ?description.
  ?condition a syn:Condition ; syn:code 'Hypertension'^xsd:string; syn:hasDiagnosed ?encounter.
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter ; syn:isPrescribedDuring ?medication ; syn:dateTime ?startDateTime.
  ?supply a syn:Supply ; syn:encounterId ?encounterId ; syn:quantity ?quantity ; syn:code 'lisinopril 10 MG Oral Tablet'^xsd:string.
  BIND(REPLACE(REPLACE(STR(?description), 'Tablet', ''), 'Oral', '') AS ?formulation)
  BIND(?quantity * 30 AS ?duration)
}
```

question: Please provide me the name of the patients related to the device Respiratory humidifier (physical object).

answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>
SELECT DISTINCT ?name  WHERE { ?device a syn:Device . ?device syn:code snomed: "232559003"^^snomed: . ?device syn:patientId ?patientId . ?patient a syn:Patient ; syn:id ?patientId; syn:first ?firstName; syn:last ?lastName.  BIND(CONCAT(str(?firstName), ' ', str(?lastName)) AS ?name)  }

question: When was the device Respiratory humidifier (physical object) implanted or initially used?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?start WHERE { ?device a syn:Device; syn:description 'Respiratory humidifier (physical object)'^^pl:; syn:startDateTime ?start. }
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 
SELECT DISTINCT ?patient 
WHERE {
  ?device a syn:Device ; syn:code "Respiratory humidifier (physical object)"^^snomed:; syn:patient ?patient . 
  OPTIONAL {?encounter a syn:Encounter ; syn:id ?deviceId ; syn:patient ?patient . ?device syn:isMeasuredBy ?patient. 
  FILTER (?encounterId = ?deviceId) . 
  ?encounter syn:startDateTime ?date .}
  OPTIONAL {?encounter a syn:Encounter ; syn:id ?encounterId . ?device syn:isOrderedDuring ?encounter . 
  FILTER (?encounterId = ?encounterId) . 
  ?encounter syn:startDateTime ?date .}
  UNION
  {?patient syn:hasDevice ?device .}
}

answers:
Here is an example of a syntactically correct SPARQL query leveraging the provided ontology, notes, and examples:

**[Question]**
Find all patients who received care at the organization with name 'General Practice A', and also have allergies to medications identified by RxNorm codes in a list provided as input via the `$medications` variable. 

**[Assumptions]**
* The `$medications` variable  contains a list of RxNorm codes separated by commas, e.g. `'945146','1365957','387250'`.
* The organization with name "General Practice A" has a unique identifier represented by the variable `$org_id`.

**[SPARQL Query]**

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>

SELECT DISTINCT ?patient ?allergy
WHERE {
  ?patient a syn:Patient .
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter ; syn:hasPatient ?patient ; syn:isPerformedAt ?organization .
  ?organization a syn:Organization ; syn:name 'General Practice A'^^pl: ; syn:id ?org_id .
  ?allergy a syn:Allergy ; syn:isAbout ?patient ; syn:isDiagnosedDuring ?encounter ; syn:code ?rxnorm_code .
  FILTER (str(?rxnorm_code) IN ( $medications )) 
}

```

This SPARQL query combines features from the provided examples and notes:

*  It employs prefixes for better readability. 
*  It constructs a SPARQL query using `SELECT DISTINCT` to retrieve unique variables as the result.
*  It uses the provided prefixes for concise syntax. 
*  It incorporates the `$medications` input variable along with the `$org_id` variable in the `FILTER` clause. 
*  It ensures the filtering criteria match the context based on the provided question and assumptions.

This example query demonstrates how to construct SPARQL queries using information from the provided ontology, notes, and examples. It serves as a template that you can adapt and build upon for generating your own queries to answer given questions.

question: What is the classification of Cows milk (substance)?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT DISTINCT ?category WHERE { ?allergy a syn:Allergy ; syn:description 'Cows milk (substance)'^^pl:; syn:category ?category; }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
SELECT DISTINCT ?description 
WHERE {
  ?allergy a syn:Allergy ;
       syn:description 'Cows milk (substance)'^^pl: ;
       syn:code ?code.
  ?allergyClass a owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf ?code .
  ?allergyClass rdfs:subClassOf ?parentClass.
  ?parentClass rdfs:subClassOf ?grandParentClass. 
  ?grandParentClass rdfs:subClassOf ?greatGrandParentClass. 
  ?grandParentClass rdfs:subClassOf ?ggParentClass.
  ?greatGrandParentClass rdfs:subClassOf ?gggParent.
  ?ggParentClass rdfs:subClassOf ?ggggParent.
  ?gggParent rdfs:subClassOf ?gggggParent.
  ?gggggParent rdfs:subClassOf ?ggggggParent.
  ?ggggggParent rdfs:subClassOf owl:Thing.
  FILTER ( ( !isBlank(?parentClass)) && ( !isBlank(?grandParentClass)) && ( !isBlank(?greatGrandParentClass)) && ( !isBlank(?ggParentClass)) && ( !isBlank(?gggParent)) && ( !isBlank(?gggggParent)))
  ?parentClass rdfs:label ?description
    FILTER ( lang(?description) = 'en' ).
}
```

question: Please provide me the number of encounters uncovered by the payer with the ID e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?uncoveredEncounters WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:id 'e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496'^^uuid:; syn:uncoveredEncounters ?uncoveredEncounters. }
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>
PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?count
WHERE { 
?payer a syn:Payer; syn:id "e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496"^^uuid.
?claim syn:isCoveredBy ?payer.
?encounter syn:hasClaim ?claim.
FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?claim syn:hasEncounter ?encounter. }
?count (COUNT(?encounter) AS ?c).
}

```{note}
- Here, **?count** is a variable representing the count of all uncovered encounters.
- The SPARQL query retrieves all uncovered encounters by looking for **encounters that belong to a payer claim but are not listed as the claim's encounter**.
- The **foaf:name** is used to distinguish patients as the SPARQL query is searching for an encounter without its own record.
- This query can be used to filter out uncovered encounters for further analysis or investigation.

SELECT ?name ?encounterId ?Encounter_Id

?Encounter_Id syn:patientId ?PatientId. 
?PatientId syn:id ?Patient_Id.

?encdescr syn:encounterId ?encounterId; syn:description ?descr . 
?encdescr rdfs:comment ?descr . 
  
  ?encounter syn:performedBy ?Provider_Id . 
?Provider_Id  syn:name ?name  . 
?encounter syn:performedAt ?Organization_id.
              
}

question: Please provide me the patients with the care plan Respiratory therapy.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT DISTINCT ?first ?last WHERE { ?careplan a syn:CarePlan; syn:description 'Respiratory therapy'^^pl:; syn:patientId ?patientid. ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientid; syn:first ?first ; syn:last ?last ; }
answers:

?carePlan <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#isAbout> ?patient . 
?patient <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#patientId> ?patientId .

question: What procedures did the patient named Claris36 Bogisich202 undergo?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?description WHERE { ?patient a syn:Patient ; syn:first 'Claris36'^^pl:; syn:last 'Bogisich202'^^pl:; syn:id ?patientid. ?procedure a syn:Procedure; syn:patientId ?patientid; syn:description ?description. }
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> 
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> 
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX> 
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI> 
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm> 
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

SELECT ?patientName ?description
WHERE {
  ?encounter syn:description ?description.
  ?encounter syn:patientId ?patientId.
  ?patient a syn:Patient.
  ?patient syn:id ?patientId; 
  syn:first ?firstName; 
  syn:last  ?lastName . 
  BIND (CONCAT(?firstName,' ',?lastName) AS ?patientName) .
  FILTER( ?description ='Laceration Repair of Lower Extremity (procedure)') . 
}

sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?revenue WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:id 'e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496'^^uuid:; syn:revenue ?revenue. }
answers:
## Answer: 

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 

SELECT DISTINCT ?payerName ?revenue 
WHERE 
{ 
  ?payer a syn:Payer ; 
         syn:id  "e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496" ;
         syn:name ?payerName ; 
         syn:revenue ?revenue . 
}
```

**Explanation:**

This SPARQL query retrieves payer name (`?payerName`) and revenue (`?revenue`) for the payer with ID "e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496".

1. `PREFIX` statements: Define prefixes for common namespaces like RDF, RDFS, and Sythesia ontology to make the query more concise. 
2. `SELECT DISTINCT` clause: Specifies that we want distinct values for the variables `?payerName` and `?revenue`. 
3. `WHERE` clause: Specifies the conditions that must hold for a solution to be returned. 
    - The main condition uses a series of triple patterns: 
        * Matches a payer instance (`?payer`) with ID "e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496". 
        * Retrieves its name and stores it as `?payerName`. 
        * Retrieves its revenue and stores it as `?revenue`. 

This query leverages the available information in the ontology to find the specific payer and its associated data. 

## Note:

This example assumes the ontology contains complete and accurate data. If the data is missing or incorrect, the query might not return accurate results.

question: Please provide me the encounters that are related to the condition with code 283385000.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?description WHERE { ?condition a syn:Condition; syn:code '283385000'^^snomed:; syn:encounterId ?encounterid. ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:id ?encounterid; syn:description ?description }
answers:
## SPARQL Query:

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 

SELECT ?encounterDescription 
WHERE 
{ 
?condition a syn:Condition ; 
syn:code "283385000"^^snomed: , ?conditionDescription. 
?encounter a syn:Encounter ; 
syn:hasDiagnosed ?condition ; 
syn:description ?encounterDescription . 
}
```

## Explanation:

1. **Prefixes:** 
    - We use the provided prefixes for better readability and efficiency.

answers:
Here's the answer to **List all patients with an allergy to dust mites who have had at least one encounter.**

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?firstName ?lastName ?allergyDescription
WHERE {
  ?allergy a syn:Allergy ;
          syn:code "44054006"^^snomed: ;
          syn:description ?allergyDescription .
  ?patient a syn:Patient ;
          syn:id ?patientId .
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter ;
          syn:patientId ?patientId .
  ?patient syn:firstName ?firstName ;
          syn:lastName ?lastName .
}
```

This SPARQL query will return a list of rows, where each row contains the first name, last name, and allergy description for patients who meet the following criteria:

* Have an allergy with the code `44054006` (which corresponds to "house dust mite allergen"),
* Have had at least one encounter.

The query uses the following prefixes:

* `rdf`: Resource Description Framework
* `rdfs`: Resource Description Framework Schema
* `syn`: Sythetic Data
* `xsd`: XML Schema Definition
* `pl`: PlainLiteral

The query uses the following variables:

* `?allergy`: represents an instance of the `syn:Allergy` class
* `?allergyDescription`: represents the description of the allergy
* `?patient`: represents an instance of the `syn:Patient` class
* `?patientId`: represents the ID of the patient
* `?encounter`: represents an instance of the `syn:Encounter` class
* `?firstName`: represents the first name of the patient
* `?lastName`: represents the last name of the patient

question: When was the imaging study with the ID 71ee50dd-ea7c-3415-e8d9-8b3a950cf731 conducted?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?dateTime WHERE { ?imagingstudy a syn:ImagingStudy; syn:id '71ee50dd-ea7c-3415-e8d9-8b3a950cf731'^^uuid:; syn:dateTime ?dateTime. }
answers:
## Synthea SPARQL Query

```sparql
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?encounter_date ?modality
WHERE {
  ?imaging_study a syn:ImagingStudy;
                 syn:id "71ee50dd-ea7c-3415-e8d9-8b3a950cf731";
                 syn:modalityCode ?modality_code.
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter;
              syn:id ?imaging_study_encounterId.
  ?imaging_study syn:encounterId ?imaging_study_encounterId.
  ?encounter syn:performedDuring ?performed_during.
  ?encounter_date syn:dateTime ?encounter_date.
  FILTER (?performed_during = ?encounter_date)
  FILTER (?modality_code = "CT") .
}
```

## Explanation

This SPARQL query retrieves the date and modality of the imaging study with the ID "71ee50dd-ea7c-3415-e8d9-8b3a950cf731".

* The query starts with the `PREFIX` declarations to define the namespaces for the prefixes used in the query.
* The `SELECT` clause specifies the variables that will be returned by the query. In this case, it retrieves the `encounter_date` and `modality` variables.
* The `WHERE` clause specifies the conditions that must be met by the data in order to be included in the results.
* The first line of the `WHERE` clause specifies that the query is looking for an instance of `syn:ImagingStudy` with the ID "71ee50dd-ea7c-3415-e8d9-8b3a950cf731". This is done by using the `a` keyword and specifying the class and the instance ID.
* The second line retrieves the modality code associated with the imaging study using the `syn:modalityCode` property.
* The third and fourth lines identify the `syn:Encounter` associated with the imaging study using the `syn:encounterId` property.
* The fifth line links the encounter date with the encounter using the `syn:performedDuring` property.
* The last two lines filter the results to only include imaging studies with the modality code "CT" and encounters that were performed on the same date as the imaging study.

## Response Format

This query will return two columns: `encounter_date` and `modality`. Each row will represent an Imaging Study that meets the specified criteria. The `encounter_date` column will contain the date of the encounter, and the `modality` column will contain the modality of the Imaging Study.

For example, if the query found an Imaging Study with the ID "71ee50dd-ea7c-3415-e8d9-8b3a950cf731", was performed on 2018-01-01, and had a modality of "CT", the result would be:

| encounter_date | modality |
|---|---|
| 2018-01-01 | CT |

# Which organization has the most patients with a diagnosis of diabetes?

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>

SELECT ?org_name ?count
WHERE 
{
    ?encounter syn:hasPatient ?patient.
    ?patient syn:hasHistoryOf ?condition.
    ?condition a syn:Condition; syn:code '44054006'^^snomed:.
    ?encounter syn:isPerformedAt ?org.
    ?org a syn:Organization; syn:name ?org_name.
    
    BIND (COUNT(?patient) AS ?count)
}
ORDER BY DESC(?count)
LIMIT 1
```

answers:
**Query:** Which patient had an encounter with a recorded SNOMED-CT code of 340654006 and an encounter with a recorded SNOMED-CT code of 55643009?
**SPARQL Query:**

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT ?patient
WHERE {
  ?allergy a syn:Allergy ;
    syn:code snomed:340654006; 
    syn:patient ?patient.
  
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter; 
    syn:code snomed:55643009;
    syn:patient ?patient. 
}
```

**Explanation:**

This query uses the `PREFIX` keyword to define the prefixes used in the query. 

The `SELECT` clause specifies that the query will return the `?patient` variable.

The `WHERE` clause contains the conditions that the query will use to find the patient. 

The first part of the `WHERE` clause finds allergies with the SNOMED-CT code `340654006` and stores the corresponding patient ID in the `?patient` variable.

The second part of the `WHERE` clause finds encounters with the SNOMED-CT code `55643009` and also stores the corresponding patient ID in the `?patient` variable.

The query then matches the `?patient` variables from both parts of the `WHERE` clause to find patients who have both allergies and encounters with the specified SNOMED-CT codes.

question: What is the encounter associated with the condition with code 444814009?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?description WHERE { ?condition a syn:Condition; syn:code '444814009'^^snomed:; syn:encounterId ?encounterid. ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:id ?encounterid; syn:description ?description }
answers:
## Finding Encounters Related to the Condition ID with Loinc Code 444814009 (Blood Glucose 2 hour Post Meal with PO Glucose [Mass/volume] in Blood)

Here's the SPARQL query for finding encounters associated with the condition with loinc code 444814009:

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?encounter ?encounterDescription ?codeDescription
WHERE 
{
  ?condition rdf:type syn:Condition; 
              syn:code '444814009'^^loinc:LOINC.     # Condition with LOINC code 444814009
  
  # Find relevant patient diagnosed during an encounter associated with the LOINC condition.
  ?patient syn:hasDiagnosed ?diagnosedCondition.    
  ?diagnosedCondition rdfs:subPropertyOf syn:isDiagnosedDuring.       
  ?diagnosedCondition syn:hasCondition ?condition.        
  
  ?encounter syn:hasPatient ?patient ; 
              syn:description ?encounterDescription.      # Extract details of related encounter
        
  # Identify the condition description with the code.       
  OPTIONAL { ?diagnosis syn:isAbout ?patient;        
              syn:description ?codeDescription ;         
              syn:isDiagnosedDuring ?diagnosedCondition.    
            }     
}
```

The query selects distinct `encounter`, `encounterDescription`, and `codeDescription`. These variables represent specific details related to the query's focus:

* **?encounter**: identifier representing the relevant encounter
* **?encounterDescription**: textual description about the encounter
* **?codeDescription**: description of diagnosis if a condition with the provided LOINC code is found (optional)

Here's a breakdown of its logic:

1. **Finding the Condition:** The code 444814009 is selected as the target condition with the `rdf:type syn:Condition; syn:code '444814009'^^loinc:LOINC` condition.
2. **Identifying Patients Diagnosed with the Condition in Encounters:** We find patients (`?patient`) who have a diagnosed condition (`?diagnosedCondition`) that is subcategorized under `isDiagnosedDuring` and contains the same condition as identified in step 1 (`diagnosis`). The `?hasDiagnosed` property connects a patient to a specific diagnosed condition within an encounter.
3. **Targeting Relevant Encounters & Descriptions:** Using the identified patients, this step extracts related `?encounters` where they were patients and provides the corresponding `?encounterDescription` for these encounters.
4. **Retrieving Optional Code Description (if available):** The optional block retrieves additional details about the diagnosed condition if it exists. If the patient has a condition (`diagnosis`) diagnosed during the selected `diagnosedCondition`, their descriptions are provided as `codeDescription`. The `isAbout` property identifies a diagnosed condition associated with a specific patient.

This query returns information about specific encounters associated with the Loinc code 444814009. By analyzing these encounters through the description information, one can learn more about the context for why this type of blood glucose measurement was ordered.

                       syn:name              ?provider_name .                          
    
}

SPARQL query, making

using

identifies 
the allergy records related to the specified encounter.
    - **Retrieving allergy information:** Within both allergy records,we retrieve the code (`?code`), description 
(`?description2`), and system/term (`?system2`) information using appropriate properties.

question: Which patients have the observation with the code 93027-1?

PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

SELECT 
DISTINCT
 ?patientName
  WHERE

     ?patient a syn:Patient ;
  syn:first ?firstName ;

question: How many medications are uncovered by the payer Medicare?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?uncoveredMedications WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'Medicare'^^pl:; syn:uncoveredMedications ?uncoveredMedications. }

PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
SELECT (count(distinct ?encounter) AS ?uncovered_encounter_count) WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer ; syn:name 'Medicare'. ?encounter a syn:Encounter. ?claim a syn:Claim ; syn:patientId ?patientId . ?claimTransaction a syn:ClaimTransaction ; syn:claimId ?claimId; syn:encounterId ?encounterId. ?encounter syn:id ?encounterId; syn:patientId ?patientId. ?medication a syn:Medication ; syn:encounterId ?encounterId. FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?claim syn:id ?claimId ; syn:encounterId ?encounterId. } }

PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

SELECT DISTINCT ?patientId ?encounterId ?firstName ?lastName WHERE {

}
```

question: How many procedures are covered by the payer Medicaid?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?coveredProcedures WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'Medicaid'^^pl:; syn:coveredProcedures ?coveredProcedures. }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?count
WHERE
{
    ?encounter a syn:Encounter ;
    syn:isPrescribedFor ?patientId.
    ?immunization syn:hasEncounter ?encounter; syn:code ?codeset .
    ?codeset rdfs:label ?descriptionLabel ;
    filter regex(?descriptionLabel, "Antiviral") .

    #Get all payers who cover this encounter.
    ?encounter syn:isCoveredBy ?idPayer .

    #Find patients with payer ID equal to "Medicaid2016".
    ?patientId syn:payerId ?idPayer ; syn:payerId ?payerid.
    ?payerid syn:id "Medicaid2016"^^xsd:string.

    #Count how many distinct patients are in this payer list.
    bind ( count(DISTINCT ?payerid) as ?count )

}

```

question: Please provide me the amount transacted with the claim transaction ID 7058cefa-ebaf-4ab6-014c-66c91fa48079.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?amount WHERE { ?claimtransaction a syn:ClaimTransaction;syn:id '7058cefa-ebaf-4ab6-014c-66c91fa48079'^^uuid:; syn:amount ?amount.}
answers:
## SPARQL Query based on your provided input:

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
SELECT DISTINCT ?amount WHERE { ?transaction a syn:ClaimTransaction; syn:id "7058cefa-ebaf-4ab6-014c-66c91fa48079"^^uuid; syn:amount ?amount. }
```

This query retrieves the `amount` associated with the `ClaimTransaction` whose ID is "7058cefa-ebaf-4ab6-014c-66c91fa48079". 

### Explanation of the Query:

1. **PREFIX declarations:**  The prefixes are declared to shorten the URIs used in the query.
2. **SELECT:** This clause specifies the information to be retrieved, which is the `amount` in this case.
3. **WHERE clause:** This clause defines the conditions to filter the data. It specifies that the retrieved information should be about a `ClaimTransaction` with ID "7058cefa-ebaf-4ab6-014c-66c91fa48079" and that the `amount` data property should be retrieved.
4. **rdf:type syn:ClaimTransaction:** This condition specifies that the returned information should be about a `ClaimTransaction`.
5. **syn:id "7058cefa-ebaf-4ab6-014c-66c91fa48079":** This condition specifies that the `ClaimTransaction` should have the ID "7058cefa-ebaf-4ab6-014c-66c91fa48079".
6. **syn:amount ?amount:** This condition retrieves the value of the `amount` data property and stores it in the variable `?amount`.

 This query provides a clear and concise way to find the information you are looking for within the context of the given ontology.

question: What encounter is associated with the supply with the code 337388004?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?description WHERE { ?supply a syn:Supply; syn:code '337388004'^^snomed:; syn:encounterId ?encounterid. ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:id ?encounterid; syn:description ?description. }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?encounterId ?encounterDescription
WHERE {
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter ;
    syn:isOrderedDuring ?supply.
  ?supply a syn:Supply ;
    syn:code "337388004"^^snomed: .
  FILTER(NOT EXISTS {
    ?encounter syn:isOrderedDuring ?otherSupply .
    ?otherSupply a syn:Supply .
  })
  ?encounter syn:id ?encounterId .
  ?encounter syn:description ?encounterDescription .
}
```

question: What is the specialty of the provider named Tanika746 Baumbach677?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?speciality WHERE { ?provider a syn:Provider; syn:name 'Tanika746 Baumbach677'^^pl:; syn:speciality ?speciality. }
answers:
## SPARQL Query:

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT DISTINCT ?speciality
WHERE {
  ?provider a syn:Provider ;
         syn:first "Tanika" ;
         syn:last "Baumbach" ;
         syn:speciality ?speciality .
}
```

## Explanation:

This query retrieves the value of the `syn:speciality` data property for the provider whose first name is "Tanika" and last name is "Baumbach". 

* The query starts with the `SELECT DISTINCT ?speciality` clause, which indicates that we want to retrieve the distinct values of the `speciality` variable.
* The `WHERE` clause specifies the conditions that the data must satisfy.
    * The first condition uses the `a` predicate to state that the variable `?provider` represents an instance of the `syn:Provider` class.
    * The second condition uses the `first` and `last` data properties to specify the first and last names of the provider, respectively. 
    * The third condition specifies that the value of the `speciality` data property for the provider is assigned to the variable `?speciality`.
* Finally, the query returns the values of the `?speciality` variable.

question: How many immunizations are uncovered by the payer with the ID e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?uncoveredImmunizations WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:id 'e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496'^^uuid:; syn:uncoveredImmunizations ?uncoveredImmunizations. }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
SELECT (count(*) as ?uncoveredImmunizations)
WHERE { 
  ?claim a syn:Claim .
  ?claim syn:id ?claimId .
  ?transaction a syn:ClaimTransaction .
  ?transaction syn:claimId ?claimId .
  ?transaction syn:claimTransactionType "ADJUSTMENT" .
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter .
  ?encounter syn:id ?claimId .
  ?imm a syn:Immunization .
  ?imm syn:encounterId ?encounterId .
  ?imm syn:payerId ?payerId .
  ?payer a syn:Payer .
  ?payer syn:id ?payerId .
  ?payer syn:id "e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496"^^uuid .
  FILTER NOT EXISTS { 
    ?encounter syn:payerId ?payerId .
  }
}
```

answers:
## Question

Give the count of the number of observations that have a measurement above 5.5 for patient with the ID 'a4a72411-3945-bd04-3fb2-bbbd27284645'.
## SPARQL query 

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 
SELECT (COUNT(?id) AS ?totalObservationsAbove5_5) WHERE { 
  ?observation a syn:Observation .
  ?observation syn:patientId 'a4a72411-3945-bd04-3fb2-bbbd27284645'^^uuid . 
  ?observation syn:value ?observationValue .
  FILTER (xsd:double(?observationValue) > 5.5)
}
```

question: What is the type of the allergy with the code 419199007?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?type WHERE { ?allergy a syn:Allergy ; syn:code '419199007'^^snomed:; syn:type ?type; }
answers:
## Synthea SPARQL Query

```sparql
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>


SELECT DISTINCT ?type ?description
WHERE {
  ?condition a syn:Condition .
  ?condition syn:code 419199007 .
  ?condition syn:type ?type .
  OPTIONAL {
    ?condition syn:description ?description .
  }
}
```

This query identifies the type and optional description of the allergy with the SNOMED-CT code 419199007. It utilizes the following elements:

* `SELECT`: Specifies the variables to be retrieved.
* `DISTINCT`: Ensures only unique results are returned.
* `?type`: Represents the variable for the type of the allergy.
* `?description`: Represents the variable for the optional description of the allergy.
* `WHERE`: Defines the conditions for selecting data.
* `?condition`: Represents a variable referencing an instance of syn:Condition.
* `?condition a syn:Condition`: Specifies that `?condition` must be an instance of the syn:Condition class.
* `?condition syn:code 419199007`: Filters `?condition` to instances where the syn:code property has the value 419199007.
* `?condition syn:type ?type`: Retrieves the value of the syn:type property for the selected `?condition` and assigns it to the variable `?type`.
* `OPTIONAL`: Indicates that the retrieval of the syn:description is optional.
* `?condition syn:description ?description`: Retrieves the value of the syn:description property for the selected `?condition` and assigns it to the variable `?description`, if available.

question: Please provide me the number of immunizations uncovered by the payer Blue Cross Blue Shield.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?uncoveredImmunizations WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'Blue Cross Blue Shield'^^pl:; syn:uncoveredImmunizations ?uncoveredImmunizations. }
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> 
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> 
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX> 
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI> 
PREFIX ct: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm> 
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC> 

SELECT ?encounterId ?encounter ?encounterDate ?description ?patientId (COUNT(*) AS ?count) WHERE { 
?patient a syn:Patient.
?patient syn:id ?patientId.
?encounter a syn:Encounter.
?encounter syn:hasPatient ?patient. 
?encounter syn:id ?encounterId.
?encounter syn:description ?description.
?encounter syn:dateTime ?encounterDate. 
?encounter syn:encounterClass ?class. 
FILTER regex(?class, "Outpatient") 
}
GROUP BY ?encounterId ?encounter ?encounterDate ?description ?patientId
ORDER BY ?encounterDate

answers:
## SPARQL query

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI> 
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC> 

SELECT DISTINCT ?conditionName 
WHERE { 
  ?patient a syn:Patient ; 
           syn:firstName 'Tomeka87' ; 
           syn:lastName 'Goldner995' ; 
           syn:id ?patientId .

           syn:patientId ?patientId ; 
           syn:code ?conditionCode . 
  BIND(str(?conditionCode) AS ?conditionName) . 
}

```

PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>

}
```

PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT (COUNT(?encounter) AS ?num_uncovered_encounters)
WHERE {
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter.
  ?encounter syn:payerId ?payerId.
  ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:id ?payerId; syn:name 'Anthem'.
  OPTIONAL { ?encounter syn:isCoveredBy ?claim. ?claim syn:payerId ?payerId. FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?encounter syn:isCoveredBy ?claim2. ?claim2 syn:payerId ?payerId. } }
  FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?encounter syn:isCoveredBy ?claim. }
}
```

question: What type of encounter is encounter 2a87aa82-ffdd-532f-c8b3-8b3f90d2b97b?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> SELECT  ?encounterClass WHERE { ?encounter a syn:Encounter; syn:id '2a87aa82-ffdd-532f-c8b3-8b3f90d2b97b'^^uuid:; syn:encounterClass ?encounterClass. }
answers:
## SPARQL Query

```sparql
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT ?encounter_type 
WHERE { 
  ?encounter a syn:Encounter;
             syn:id "2a87aa82-ffdd-532f-c8b3-8b3f90d2b97b";
             syn:encounterClass ?encounter_type.
}
```

## Explanation:

The query starts with the definition of the relevant prefixes, as you provided them in your input. 

Then, it utilizes the `SELECT DISTINCT` clause to retrieve distinct values for the variable `?encounter_type`. The variable represents the encounter type associated with a specific encounter identified by its unique ID, `"2a87aa82-ffdd-532f-c8b3-8b3f90d2b97b"`.

The `WHERE` clause describes a pattern to match specific entities in the knowledge graph based on the input question. 

* The pattern starts by defining a variable `?encounter` that represents an entity of type `syn:Encounter`. 
* Then, the pattern restricts this `?encounter` by stating that its ID should match the given ID, `"2a87aa82-ffdd-532f-c8b3-8b3f90d2b97b"`. 
* Lastly, the pattern retrieves the value of the `syn:encounterClass` attribute for this specific `?encounter` and assigns the value to the `?encounter_type` variable.

This pattern effectively identifies the encounter with the given ID and then extracts its associated encounter class, which represents its type. 

## Output: 

The output of this query will be a single cell containing the encounter type associated with the specific encounter identified by the given ID. For instance, the output could be `Ambulatory` if the encounter belonged to the ambulatory care setting.

question: What is the reason code for the procedure Urine screening test for diabetes?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?reasoncode WHERE { ?procedure a syn:Procedure; syn:description 'Urine screening test for diabetes'^^pl:; syn:reasoncode ?reasoncode. }
answers:
```sparql
#PREFIX to be defined to reduce verbosity
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> 
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> 
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> 
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid> 
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX> 
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI> 
PREFIX ct: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm> 
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

#Find encounters that had their main diagnosis 'Urine screening test for diabetes'
SELECT DISTINCT ?encounterId ?encounterDescription
WHERE {
    ?encounter a syn:Encounter; 
    syn:encounterId ?encounterId; 
    syn:description ?encounterDescription; 
    syn:isDiagnosedDuring ?condition; 
    syn:code '23641-5'. #ICD-10 code: Urine screening test for diabetes
    FILTER (regex(STR(?encounterDescription), ".*Diabetes.*", "i")) #Include encounters containing the word "Diabetes" in the description
}
```

question: How many medications are uncovered by the payer Aetna?

answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
SELECT DISTINCT ?patientId ?firstName ?lastName
WHERE {
?medication syn:code '170230'^^<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>. 
?medication  syn:id  ?medicationId.  
?encounter syn:hasPrescribedDuring ?medicationId. 
?encounter  syn:patient  ?patientId.  
?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientId; syn:first ?firstName ; syn:last ?lastName . 

?encounter syn:id ?encId; syn:isCoveredDuring ?payerId. 
?medication syn:payerId ?payerId ; syn:isUncoveredBy ?payerId ; syn:id ?medicationId1.
  FILTER (?medicationId != ?medicationId1) 
}
